But the threshold case matters: for many agent deployments, the alternative to imperfect internal separation is not regulatory authorization - it is no authorization at all. The human owner is the practical issuer in most current systems, and the human bears residual liability whether or not they are named in the record. The gap is not that the ideal authorization model is being implemented incorrectly - it is that most systems never adopted any authorization model beyond credential issuance.

